---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Use"
  description="Terms of use for Korea Travel Guide."
>
  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
      <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
      <p>Last updated: 2026-07-21</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <article class="article wrap">
    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        By using Korea Travel Guide (the "Site"), you agree to these terms.
        Please read them before relying on any information here.
      </p>

      <h2>Informational purpose only</h2>
      <p>
        Content on this Site is provided for general informational purposes.
        Travel details — opening hours, prices, availability, visa and entry
        rules, and emergency procedures — change frequently. We do our best to
        keep information current and to source facts from reliable data, but we
        make no warranty that any information is accurate, complete, or up to
        date. Always verify with official sources before you travel or make
        decisions.
      </p>

      <h2>No professional advice</h2>
      <p>
        Nothing on this Site is legal, immigration, medical, or financial
        advice. For visa, health, or safety matters, consult the relevant
        official authority or a qualified professional.
      </p>

      <h2>AI assistance</h2>
      <p>
        Our guides are produced with AI assistance and reviewed against data
        sources. We disclose this on our articles and in our
        <a href="/about">editorial policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Third-party links & content</h2>
      <p>
        The Site links to third-party websites and services and may display
        licensed third-party images. We are not responsible for the content,
        policies, or availability of external sites.
      </p>

      <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the extent permitted by law, we are not liable for any loss or
        damage arising from your use of, or reliance on, this Site.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>Questions about these terms? See our <a href="/contact">contact page</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
